<?xml version="1.0"?>
<CP_Scriptfile date="Nov 6, 2011">
<CPscript title="Empty script for editing" >
<text> This is an annulus with two symmetries, translational and reflective. With symmetric branching at 1 and 43, packs without holonomy. </text>
<cmd iconname="list.png">Cleanse;act0; infile_read a0.p;layout;Disp -w -c -cf 1 43 -R </cmd>
<cmd iconname="delete.png">act 0;set_aim 4.0 1 43;repack;layout;disp -wr </cmd>
<text> With broken symmetry, Crane adds shepherd circles and gets this result. </text>
<cmd iconname="dnd_multi.png">act 0; </cmd>
<text> Now, we have broken the translational (vertical) symmetry. Will try to fix by moving the branch point at 1 so holonomy vanishes </text>
<cmd iconname="debugger.png">act1;infile_read broken.p;layout;Disp -w -c -cf 1 43 -R;set_vlist 1 43;copy 2;write -S test.p;copy 0;act 0;extender -x;extender fb;set_aim 4.0 1 43;repack;fix;layout </cmd>
<cmd iconname="network.png">act1;infile_read broken.p;write -S test.p;extender -x;extender fb;|fb| exp_DAF_shift 1 2 43 0 50000; </cmd>
<text> lowest Error = 0.016654238604325567 |fb| spt 0.007264846790176804 0.9172514251670904 1 ; |fb| spt 1.2911445264505683 0.8978480886261184 43;

lowest Error = 0.016896184128072395 |fb| spt 0.02774500284326553 0.9164155963517253 1 ; |fb| spt 0.7814193641910037 0.9224130885206957 43; </text>
<cmd iconname="metacontact_offline.png">act 2;extender -x fb;extender fb;set_aim 4.0 43 1;repack;layout;disp;S:=1.0; </cmd>
<cmd inline="no" name="a" mnemonic="a" iconname="idea.png">act 2;|fb| spt 0.00 0.9164155963517253 2 1;|fb| riff 300;|fb| lay;disp;|fb| sdisp -lc; </cmd>
<cmd inline="no" name="d" mnemonic="d" iconname="xeyes.png">layout;Disp -w -c -cf 1 43 -R; </cmd>
  </CPscript>
